INSTALLATION on Centos 7.6.1810

# useradd mediabot

Mediabot need several perl modules from cpan to run, they will be install as root user in order to be available for every user of the system
That's why it needs a temporary sudo access, to do so visudo is used
If you prefer nano as an editor instead of vi, type the following commands before visudo
(Thanks to Hero on Undernet who made me add this)

(optional) # yum install nano
(optional) # export EDITOR=/usr/bin/nano

# visudo

add this line (which MUST be removed after installation) :

mediabot ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD:ALL

# yum install git
# yum install cpan
# yum install gcc
# yum install mariadb-server
# systemctl enable mariadb
# systemctl start mariadb
# su - mediabot
$ git clone https://github.com/teuk/mediabot_v3
$ cd mediabot_v3
$ ./configure

If everything's ok then test in foreground using your config file e.g :

$ ./mediabot.pl --conf=mediabot.conf

To run the bot in daemon mode :

$ ./mediabot.pl --conf=mediabot.conf --daemon
